      <td><strong>Pilot w/ Contour3D</strong></td><td>$0</td><td>$278–358k</td><td>$70–125k</td><td>$14–36k</td><td><strong>$362–519k</strong></td><td><strong>$434–623k</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Pilot w/ CyBe</strong></td><td>$100–120k</td><td>$278–358k</td><td>$70–125k</td><td>$14–36k</td><td><strong>$462–639k</strong></td><td><strong>$554–767k</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Pilot w/ Luyten</strong></td><td>$345–595k</td><td>$278–358k</td><td>$70–125k</td><td>$14–36k</td><td><strong>$707–1,114k</strong></td><td><strong>$848–1,337k</strong></td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout good">
  <strong>Break-even (CyBe):</strong> At $280/m² savings vs traditional wall construction, the €49k printer pays for itself after 357–429 m² of printed wall — approximately 5–6 dwellings. Luyten needs 18–30 dwellings.
</div>

<!-- ======================================================================= -->
<!-- 8. REGULATORY PATHWAY                                                   -->
<!-- ======================================================================= -->
<h2><span class="num">8</span> Regulatory pathway</h2>
<p>3DCP qualifies as a <strong>Performance Solution</strong> under NCC A2G2. No Deemed‑to‑Satisfy provision exists yet, so the path is well-defined through an Evidence-of-Suitability dossier.</p>

<ol class="steps">
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Identify Performance Requirements</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Map H1P1 (structure), H2P1 (fire), H3P1 (weatherproofing), H4P1 (energy), H5P1 (sound) to your 3DCP wall system.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Material qualification testing</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Engage ULTRA Labs or RMIT for a full NATA test suite: compressive, inter‑layer bond, FRL, water penetration, thermal conductivity, airborne sound. Budget <strong>$8,800–21,000</strong>.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Compile Evidence-of-Suitability dossier</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Structure the dossier per the template: project description → performance matrix → test reports → structural engineer certificate → G‑code spec → QA plan.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Engage a certifier early</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Pre-engagement by Month 2. Warne Properties Unit can recommend certifiers who've assessed 3DCP. Involve certifier at design stage — don't design to DTS and hope.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Obtain Construction Certificate + Occupation Certificate</div>
    <div class="step-desc">DA (Month 6–10) → CC (Month 10–12) → Print with in‑process inspection → OC (Month 16–18).</div>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="callout warn">
  <strong>Key risk:</strong> Certifier hesitancy due to novelty. Mitigate by leveraging Warne Properties' existing 3DCP work and preparing the full EoS dossier before submitting the CC application.
</div>

<!-- ======================================================================= -->
<!-- 9. IMMEDIATE ACTION PLAN                                                -->
<!-- ======================================================================= -->
<h2><span class="num">9</span> Immediate action plan</h2>

<ol class="steps">
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Contact Contour3D</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Reach out via contour3d.com.au. Reference the James Hardie social‑housing pilot. Propose a specific second pilot — your design, their print. Request Woolooware site visit.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Shortlist CyBe for R&amp;D printer</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Request a demo unit shipped to Sydney. At €49k it's negligible compared to build costs and gives you in‑house mix trial capability.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Engage ULTRA Labs for test quotes</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Request a quote for the full EoS test suite: compressive, bond, FRL, water penetration, thermal, sound. Budget $8,800–21,000.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Contact Warne Properties Unit</div>
    <div class="step-desc">NSW Planning — they can provide compliance pathway guidance and certifier recommendations based on their existing 3DP social housing pilot.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Prepare grant application</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Target NSW Affordable Housing Innovation Fund ($50k–500k) and NSW Building Innovation Fund ($100k–1M). Template available in <a href="grant-proposal-template.md" style="color:var(--accent)">grant-proposal-template.md</a>.</div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="step-title">Generate pilot G-code from BIM model</div>
    <div class="step-desc">Once the design is ready, run it through <code>bim2print</code>. The pipeline already handles walls with openings, columns, and multiple profiles — verified with 720 layers, 56k moves, 3 profiles.</div>
  </li>
</ol>

